      "kind": "drift-fix",
      "auto_safe": false,
      "priority": "P3",
      "status": "done",
      "completed": "2026-05-21",
      "result": "Added Sync-PackageJsonVersion function to scripts/release.ps1: reads BUILD_VERSION from src/profile.ts and rewrites package.json to match before each push. Runs ahead of Test-YacIntegrity which then verifies they match. package.json bumped 0.26.0 -> 0.28.6 in the same ship to backfill the drift. Shipped in 0.28.6.",
      "prompt": "YaC has two version sources, CONTEXT.md and package.json. They drift because release.ps1 only touches CONTEXT.md. Add a step to release.ps1 (or push-to-github.ps1) that reads CONTEXT.md current version pill, parses X.Y.Z, runs pnpm version <ver> --no-git-tag-version so package.json moves in lockstep. The 2026-05-15 bump to 0.26.0 was hand-applied; future bumps should be automatic.",
      "source": "2026-05-15 anti-drift analysis"
    },
    {
      "id": "yae-artifact-session-path-hardcode-019",
      "added": "2026-05-15T20:00",
      "project": "yae",
      "kind": "structural",
      "auto_safe": false,
      "priority": "P1",
      "status": "in-progress",
      "attempts": 1,
      "prompt": "The cross-project-status artifact hardcodes the previous session VM mount root. Each Cowork session gets a new mount root, so the live-refresh git + queue + audit panels silently fail. Fix: discover the mount root dynamically at refresh time via ls -d /sessions/*/mnt/YesAndEverything 2>/dev/null | head -1, then substring-extract the session segment, then build all per-repo paths from that base. Apply to all five hardcoded path references in the artifact JS.",
      "source": "2026-05-15 queue-drain-frequent run"
    },
    {
